<div class="intro-pull"><strong>Your dog is part of the trip.</strong> Best Western Vernal Inn is one of the few full-service hotels in Vernal that welcomes pets. Ground-floor rooms make it easy to take your dog out without navigating stairs or elevators. The hotel is surrounded by open space, and Vernal's location at the edge of the Uinta Basin puts you within minutes of dog-friendly trails, parks, and public lands. A small pet fee applies — call (435) 789-6625 for details.</div>
<div class="content-section">
 <h2>What Pet Owners Need to Know</h2>
<p>We keep our pet policy simple. Dogs are welcome. A small pet fee applies per stay. Ground-floor rooms are available for easy outdoor access. There's open space around the property for walks and bathroom breaks. And because Vernal sits at the gateway to millions of acres of public land, your dog has more room to run here than just about anywhere in Utah.</p>
<ul class="feat-list">
 <li>Dogs welcome — small pet fee applies</li>
 <li>Ground-floor rooms available for easy outdoor access</li>
 <li>Open space around the property for walks</li>
 <li>Near hiking trails, parks, and public lands</li>
 <li>Kitchenettes available — bring your dog's food and prep easily</li>
 <li>Free parking — room for the dog crate in the vehicle</li>
 <li>24-hour front desk — late arrivals with pets are fine</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="content-section">
 <h2>Dog-Friendly Things to Do Near the Hotel</h2>
<p>Vernal is an outdoor town, and most of the public lands surrounding it are dog-friendly. Dogs on leash are welcome at Red Fleet State Park (12 miles north), on BLM lands throughout the Uintah Basin, and on most Ashley National Forest trails. Dinosaur National Monument has limited pet access — dogs are allowed in campgrounds and on paved areas but not on backcountry trails.</p>
<ul class="feat-list">
 <li>Red Fleet State Park — 12 miles, dogs on leash welcome</li>
 <li>Ashley National Forest trails — 15 miles to the boundary</li>
 <li>BLM public lands — open access throughout the basin</li>
 <li>Vernal city parks — nearby green space for quick walks</li>
 <li>Steinaker State Park — 7 miles, dogs on leash allowed</li>
 <li>Dinosaur National Monument — limited access, campgrounds only</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="pro-tip"><p><strong>Pet Owner Tip:</strong> If you're visiting Red Fleet or Ashley National Forest with your dog, book a ground-floor kitchenette room. You'll have easy in-and-out access, space to prep dog food, and a fridge to store treats and water bottles.</p></div>
